<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <%- include('partials/head') %>
</head>
<body>
  <%- include('partials/cursor') %>
  <%- include('partials/nav') %>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="story-hero">
    <div class="story-hero-img-wrap">
      <img src="/images/flatwarming-18.jpg" alt="The Flatwarming — Beautiful Sunday's Film Club" class="story-hero-img">
      <div class="story-hero-overlay"></div>
    </div>
    <div class="story-hero-content reveal">
      <span class="story-hero-category">Films</span>
      <h1 class="story-hero-title">'The Flatwarming' Secures Screening at Beautiful Sunday's Film Club</h1>
      <span class="story-hero-date">September 2025</span>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Article -->
  <section class="story-body">
    <div class="story-body-inner reveal">
      <p>The Flatwarming has been selected for an intimate screening at the Beautiful Sunday's Film Club, marking a proud moment for the team at Braxton Studios. Held at the historic Old Toll Bar in Glasgow, the event offered a unique opportunity for local audiences to experience the film in a setting that perfectly complemented its character-driven narrative. The evening served as a celebration of independent cinema, allowing for direct engagement between the filmmakers and the local creative community in an authentic, atmospheric environment.</p>

      <p>This physical screening follows a highly successful digital launch on YouTube during the festive period, which saw the film reach a significant audience in record time. In its first two weeks of release, The Flatwarming garnered over 6,000 unique viewers, demonstrating a strong appetite for high-tier independent storytelling. The digital success of the project highlights the studio's ability to build momentum across platforms, bridging the gap between traditional cinema experiences and global digital distribution.</p>

      <div class="story-inline-img">
        <img src="/images/flatwarming-trio.jpg" alt="The Flatwarming — on set">
      </div>

      <p>The film itself is a nuanced exploration of friendship and the underlying tensions that surface when personal success intersects with social dynamics. Set during a housewarming party in a new flat, the story delves into the complexities of young adulthood and the friction created by differing levels of privilege. As the characters navigate uncomfortable honesty and long-standing grievances, the film captures the raw energy of modern relationships through sharp dialogue and intimate cinematography.</p>

      <p>As Braxton Studios continues to grow, the journey of The Flatwarming serves as a prime example of our mission to make high-tier production and platform growth effortless. By successfully managing both a prestigious local screening and a high-impact digital premiere, we have shown how strategic planning can elevate the reach of creative vision. We look forward to applying these insights to our upcoming projects as we continue to support our clients and partners on a global scale.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <%- include('partials/signup') %>
  <%- include('partials/footer') %>
  <%- include('partials/scripts') %>
</body>
</html>
